<figureCitation box="[212,282,739,764]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Meschia pugnax, male: 5, abdominal dorsum; 6, abdominal venter; 7, pygophore, dorsal view; 8, left paramere; 9, adeagus; 10, aedeagus, basal part; 11, aedeagus, apical part; 12, ejaculatory reservoir, enlarged. Abbreviations: b, body; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; hp, helicoid process; ph, phallotheca; w, wing; III-VII, abdominal tergites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252244/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">
Fig. 
<number box="[265,282,739,764]" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
. Venter slightly fuscous (
<figureCitation box="[569,638,739,764]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Meschia pugnax, male: 5, abdominal dorsum; 6, abdominal venter; 7, pygophore, dorsal view; 8, left paramere; 9, adeagus; 10, aedeagus, basal part; 11, aedeagus, apical part; 12, ejaculatory reservoir, enlarged. Abbreviations: b, body; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; hp, helicoid process; ph, phallotheca; w, wing; III-VII, abdominal tergites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252244/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">
